Explanation:

I examined controllers/profile.js and focused on the deleteProfile handler which is invoked for DELETE requests to /profiles/{id}. The function:

- extracts the path parameter id (req.params.id).
- validates the id using mongoose.Types.ObjectId.isValid(id) and returns status 404 with a plain text message ("No profile with id: <id>") if invalid.
- calls ProfileModel.findByIdAndRemove(id) to delete the document.
- responds with a JSON object { message: "Profile deleted successfully." } (no explicit status, so default 200).

From that I infer the required OpenAPI Operation object should declare:
- a required path parameter "id" of type string (MongoDB ObjectId).
- a 200 response with application/json content containing an object with a "message" string.
- a 404 response for invalid id (and potential not-found cases) with text/plain content (matching the .send() usage) and also allow an application/json variant (other controllers sometimes use JSON messages).

I set operationId to deleteProfile and included a brief summary and description that correspond to the code behavior.

